text: Kalmar BTK is a table tennis club in the town of Kalmar in Sweden. It was established on 14 June 1960. The club won the Swedish national men's team championship in the years of 1996, 1999, 2000 and 2002. Jan-Ove Waldner played for the club between 1996 and 2006. ==References== ==Other websites== *Official website Category:1960 establishments in Europe Category:Table tennis clubs in Sweden Category:1960s establishments in Sweden
